<subsection xml:id="subsec-velocity-and-acceleration">
    <title>velocity and acceleration in different situations</title>

    <p>
        <m>Velocity </m> is speed in a specified direction 
    </p>
    <p>
        Velocity differs from speed as it includes direction.
    </p>
    <p>
        Symbol of velocity is given as <m>V</m> while speed is given as <m>S</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <m> v = \frac{d}{t} </m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>Acceleration</m> - The rate of change of velocity with time. and the symbol is  <m>a</m>. and SI unit is <m>m/s²</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Acceleration is given by
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow>\textbf{Acceleration} \, = \frac{\textbf{Change in velocity}}{\textbf{Time Taken}} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
     <p>
        <m> a = \frac{\Delta v}{\Delta t} </m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Negative acceleration is called <m>\textbf{ ( deceleration or retardation)}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        For motion with constant acceleration, the three equations of motion are:
    </p>
    <p>
        <m> v = u + at </m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Final velocity = Initial velocity + (acceleration <m> \times </m> time)
    </p>
     <p>
         <m> s = ut + \frac{1}{2} at^2 </m>
    </p>
     <p>
        Displacement = <m>(initial velocity \times time) + (½ \times acceleration \times time²) </m>
    </p>
    
    <p>
        Final velocity² = Initial velocity² + (2 <m>\times</m> acceleration <m>\times</m> displacement)
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{red} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            A car accelerates from <m>\textbf{75 km/h}</m> to <m>\textbf{90 km/h}</m> in <m>\textbf{10 seconds}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Find it's acceleration
        </p>
        
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A rocket accelerates from rest to <m>\textbf{250 m/s in 10 seconds}</m>. Calculate the rocket's acceleration.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Initial velocity  <m>\textbf{(v₀) = 0 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Final velocity  <m>\textbf{(v) = 250 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Time (t) = <m>\textbf{10 seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Acceleration (a) = (v - v₀) / t
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{\textbf{(v - v₀)}}{t} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(250 m/s - 0 m/s)}}{\textbf{10 seconds}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(250 m/s)}}{\textbf{10 seconds}}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\textbf{ a = 25 m/s²}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                The rocket's acceleration is <m>\textbf{25 m/s²}</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                An object decelerates from 20 m/s to 5 m/s in 3 seconds. What is its acceleration?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Initial velocity  <m>\textbf{(v₀) = 20 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Final velocity  <m>\textbf{(v) = 5 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Time (t) = <m>\textbf{3 seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Acceleration (a) = (v - v₀) / t
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{\textbf{(v - v₀)}}{t} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(5 m/s - 20 m/s)}}{\textbf{3 seconds}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(-15 m/s)}}{\textbf{3 seconds}}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\textbf{ a = - m/s²}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                The object's acceleration is  <m>\textbf{ -5 m/s²}</m>. The negative sign indicates deceleration (slowing down).
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <p>
        <m>{\color{red} \textbf{Exercise}}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A car's velocity changes from <m>\textbf{10 m/s to 30 m/s}</m> in <m>4</m> seconds. Find its acceleration.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A car moves with <m>\textbf{8 m/s²} }</m> acceleration for <m>5</m> seconds, reaching <m>\textbf{40 m/s}</m>. Find its initial velocity.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A train moving at <m>\textbf{ 40 km/h }</m> decelerates at <m>\textbf{0.5 m/s² }</m>.  Find the time taken to stop
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A cyclist's speed increases from <m>\textbf{ 5 m/s to 17 m/s }</m>  over a period of <m>\textbf{ 6 seconds }</m> . What is the cyclist's average acceleration?
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A runner's velocity changes from  <m>\textbf{ 3 m/s to 7 m/s }</m>. What is the runner's average velocity?
                </p>
            </li>

        </ol>
    </p>







